# FSD — Frontend Architecture

## Layer Import Rule

A module can ONLY import from layers strictly below it. Never sideways, never up.

```
app      → pages, widgets, features, entities, shared
pages    → widgets, features, entities, shared
widgets  → features, entities, shared
features → entities, shared
entities → shared
shared   → (nothing above)
```

Slices on the same layer CANNOT import each other.
`app/` and `shared/` have no slices — segments directly.

## Slice Structure

Every slice follows the pattern: `layer/slice-name/` with segments inside.

```
entities/issue/
├── index.ts          # public API — only this is importable from outside
├── api/index.ts      # React Query hooks (useQuery/useMutation)
├── lib/index.ts      # pure helpers, computations, formatters
├── model/index.ts    # Zustand store (rare — only project has one)
└── ui/               # presentational components
    ├── flow-bar.tsx
    └── issue-header.tsx
```

Not every slice needs all segments. Use only what's needed:
- **api** — when slice fetches data (almost always in entities)
- **ui** — when slice has visual components
- **model** — when slice owns persistent UI state (Zustand). Rare.
- **lib** — pure functions, computations, color mappings

## Public API (index.ts)

Every slice MUST have `index.ts` at its root. Explicit named re-exports only.

```typescript
// ✅ entities/issue/index.ts
export { useIssues, useIssue } from "./api";
export { computeIssueMetrics, getStatusBadgeVariant } from "./lib";
export type { IssueMetrics } from "./lib";
export { FlowBar } from "./ui/flow-bar";

// ❌ NEVER
export * from "./api";
export * from "./ui";
```

External code imports ONLY from the slice root:
```typescript
import { useIssues, FlowBar } from "@/entities/issue";     // ✅
import { useIssues } from "@/entities/issue/api";           // ❌
import { FlowBar } from "@/entities/issue/ui/flow-bar";     // ❌
```

Within a slice, use relative paths:
```typescript
// entities/issue/ui/flow-bar.tsx
import { computeIssueMetrics } from "../lib";  // ✅ relative within slice
import { computeIssueMetrics } from "@/entities/issue";  // ❌ circular via index
```

## React Query Conventions

Query hooks live in `entities/*/api/index.ts`. Pattern:

```typescript
import { useQuery } from "@tanstack/react-query";
import { api } from "@/shared/api";

export function useIssues(filters: Partial<IssueFilters> = {}) {
  return useQuery({
    queryKey: ["issues", filters],
    queryFn: () => api.issues.list(filters),
  });
}
```

Rules:
- Hook name: `use` + entity noun (`useIssues`, `useSprintBurndown`)
- Query key: `[entity, ...params]` — include params for auto-refetch on change
- `queryFn` calls methods on `api` object from `@/shared/api`
- Types come from `@jira-board/shared` (Zod-inferred)
- Mutations for settings/mapping live in `features/*/api` or `features/*/ui` (with `useMutation` inline)

## Zustand Conventions

Zustand stores live in `model/index.ts`. Only for UI-only state.

```typescript
import { create } from "zustand";
import { persist } from "zustand/middleware";

export const useProjectStore = create<ProjectStore>()(
  persist(
    (set) => ({
      selectedProject: null,
      setSelectedProject: (project) => set({ selectedProject: project }),
    }),
    { name: "jira-bi:selected-project" },
  ),
);
```

Rules:
- NEVER duplicate server data in Zustand — that's React Query's job
- `persist` with `name: "jira-bi:*"` prefix for localStorage key
- Exported via slice's `index.ts`

## Layer Purpose Cheatsheet

| Layer | What belongs here | Imports from |
|-------|------------------|-------------|
| **shared/ui** | Primitives: Button, Card, Skeleton, Select, ChartContainer | nothing above |
| **shared/api** | `api` object, `http` client, `ApiError` | shared/config |
| **shared/lib** | `cn()`, `format`, `chart-theme` | nothing above |
| **entities** | Business data hooks + entity UI cards. One slice per domain concept | shared |
| **features** | User actions: filter-issues, sync-project, map-status-phase | entities, shared |
| **widgets** | Composed dashboard blocks: sprint-burndown, issues-table, filters-panel | features, entities, shared |
| **pages** | Route-level components, compose widgets | widgets, features, entities, shared |

## Creating New Code — Decision Tree

- **New API endpoint consumer?** → `entities/*/api` (query hook) or `shared/api` (api object method)
- **New computed value / formatter?** → `entities/*/lib` or `shared/lib`
- **New card/chart for dashboard?** → `widgets/new-widget/ui/index.tsx`
- **New user action (button + mutation)?** → `features/new-feature/`
- **New reusable UI primitive?** → `shared/ui/component-name.tsx`
- **New page?** → `pages/new-page/ui/index.tsx` + `pages/new-page/index.ts` + add route in `app/router.tsx`

## shared/ui Import Pattern

Heavy components are imported directly to aid tree-shaking:
```typescript
import { Card, CardHeader, Skeleton } from "@/shared/ui";             // barrel OK for basics
import { ChartContainer } from "@/shared/ui/chart-container";          // direct for heavy
import { MultiSelect } from "@/shared/ui/multi-select";                // direct for heavy
```

## Widget Pattern

One component per widget. Fetches its own data via entity hooks. Self-contained.

```typescript
// widgets/sprint-burndown/ui/index.tsx
import { useSprintBurndown } from "@/entities/sprint";
import { Card, CardContent, CardHeader, CardTitle, Skeleton } from "@/shared/ui";
import { ChartContainer } from "@/shared/ui/chart-container";

export function SprintBurndown({ sprintId }: { sprintId: string }) {
  const { data, isLoading } = useSprintBurndown(sprintId);
  return (
    <Card>
      <CardHeader><CardTitle>Burndown</CardTitle></CardHeader>
      <CardContent>
        {isLoading ? <BurndownSkeleton /> : /* chart */ null}
      </CardContent>
    </Card>
  );
}

// widgets/sprint-burndown/index.ts
export { SprintBurndown } from "./ui";
```
